icant improvement\n$\\Delta\\chi^2=-5.4$ with 2 extra parameters. For comparison, we find that the\n$\\Delta N_{\\rm eff}$ model gives $H_0=70.08_{-0.95}^{+0.91}~\\text{km/s/Mpc}$\nand $\\Delta\\chi^2=-3.4$ at the cost of one extra parameter, which disfavors the\n$\\Lambda$CDM limit just above 2$\\sigma$, since $\\Delta N_{\\rm\neff}=0.34_{-0.16}^{+0.15}$. Overall, our varying $G_N$ model performs similarly\nto the $\\Delta N_{\\rm eff}$ model in respect to the $H_0$ tension, if a\nphysical mechanism to remove PN constraints can be implemented.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 10 Apr 2020 14:28:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 11 Nov 2020 17:45:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-25"}
